<h5>
Presentation 4: Celebrity ‘Hegans’: A Critical Feminist Analysis of
YouTube Animal Advocates
</h5>
<p>
Author: Cressida Wilson<br>
Speaker: Cressida Wilson (University of Canterbury)</p>
<h5>Abstract</h5>
<p>
The broad focus of my research is how gender and animal advocacy
intersect. One aspect of the gendered nature of animal activism is that the
most celebrated activists in animal advocacy tend to be white men; this is
not representative of the diversity found in grassroots activist networks. In
order to better understand how and why gendered forms of animal
advocacy are celebrated within activist networks, I thematically analyse the
most popular YouTube animal advocates. Understanding the forms of
animal advocacy which are most legitimised will give insight into the
context within which grassroots activists are engaging in activism. Utilising
an intersectional feminist perspective I uncover some of the marginalisation
that occurs within animal advocacy networks. I conclude by discussing how
my research has implications not only for activists who are marginalized by
gender, but also by race, disability, class, and sexuality.
</p>

